answers.answer: There are many signs of preeclampsia that are regular pregnancy symptoms. .. the best thing to do is have the doctor do testing

question: Ok so triage thinks I'm borderline preeclamptic. I was doing some research about signs and noticed swollen feet are one of the symptoms for it. I noticed that my feet have swelled a whole lot about three weeks ago and mentioned that they were at my apartment and the doc kinda just shrugged it off. Should they have done blood work or anything then? But thankfully I was there today and they're testing for it. So tomorrow I get to go back and have more tests done...
